Mouse Button Tester
===================
A simple desktop tool to check for double-clicks.

Requirements
------------
Python 3.x

Linux (tkinter is not always bundled):
  sudo apt install python3-tk        # Debian/Ubuntu
  sudo dnf install python3-tkinter   # Fedora/RHEL
  sudo pacman -S tk                  # Arch

Windows/macOS: tkinter is bundled with Python by default.

Usage
-----
1. Run: python mouse_double_click_test.py
2. Set the double-click threshold (10–1000 ms): any two clicks within this interval are counted as a double-click.
3. Click anywhere inside the box to register clicks.
4. Use "Reset stats" to clear the counters, or "Clear log" to clear the event log.
